         <p class="breadcrumbs">You are here: <a href="/en.html?id=4">Government.no</a> / <a href="/en/dep/aid.html?id=165">Ministry of Labour</a> / <a href="/en/dep/aid/topics.html?id=167">Topics</a> / <span>Welfare policy</span>
</p>
         <div class="documentTop SubjectPage">            
                     
            <h1>Welfare policy</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"></div>
            <p class="textIngress">Everyone shall have equal opportunities, rights and obligations to take part in society and make use of their resources, irrespective of economic or social background. The Government’s overriding long-term goal is to rid society of poverty, and it wishes to improve the living conditions and opportunities available to those members of society who have the lowest income and the poorest living conditions.</p>
            
            <div class="descriptionTextFull"><p><img style="WIDTH: 150px; HEIGHT: 113px" alt="Welfare policy" src="/Upload/AID/temabilder/velferd/tema_velferd01_150x113.jpg" align="left" />The Government will pursue a policy aimed at reducing social differences. The efforts to combat poverty include measures involving the areas of responsibility of several sector ministries. The Ministry of Labour is responsible for follow-up vis-à-vis the municipalities with respect to the Social Services Act chapter 5 on Financial Support and section 4-5 on Temporary Accommodation. <br /><br />It is an important goal of welfare policy that as many occupationally disabled people as possible are able to provide for themselves through paid employment. This entails responsibility for the schemes relating to medical and occupational rehabilitation, for sickness benefit and disability benefit/pensions, benefits for single parents and coordination and follow-up of the Inclusive Workplace Agreement. Work on welfare policy also includes administrative responsibility for the subordinate institutions, the National Insurance Appeals Court and the new Norwegian Labour and Welfare Service (NAV).</p></div>
	    <div style="clear:both"></div>
	      
         </div>
         
         
                                
        
        
        
                            
    <div id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_divPageContent" class="documentBody">  
                

<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/AID/publikasjoner/rapporter_og_planer/2008/Action_plan_poverty_100x75.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/aid/doc/rapporter_planer/planer/2008/action-plan-against-poverty-2008.html?id=531068">Action Plan against Poverty - Status 2008 and intensified efforts 2009</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               In this action plan against poverty, the Government is presenting the status of the efforts to reduce poverty and proposing new priority areas and measures for 2009.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        
        
        
        <div class="ArticleContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/aid/topics/welfare-policy/midtspalte/areas-of-responsibility-and-policy-instr.html?id=458372">Areas of responsibility and policy instruments</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               Welfare policy instruments include measures under the responsibility of several sector ministries. The Ministry of Labour is also responsible for subordinate agencies and institutions.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/velferd/tema_velferd_avi_100x75.jpg" alt="Arbeid, velferd og inkludering" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/aid/topics/welfare-policy/midtspalte/labour-welfare-and-social-inclusion.html?id=438682">Labour, welfare and social inclusion</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               In autumn 2006, Minister of Labour and Social Inclusion Bjarne Håkon Hanssen presented the Government’s proposal for new measures in the labour and welfare administration.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        
        
        
        <div class="ArticleContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/aid/topics/welfare-policy/midtspalte/financial-social-assistance.html?id=86000">Financial social assistance</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               As a result of their responsibility for preventing social problems and improving living conditions for the disadvantaged, the social services are an important player in the efforts against poverty.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    

